  <activityInformation><![CDATA[<p>Things to do in Cernobbio</p>
<p>Despite it city status, this is a quiet place where what “life” there is revolves around a pretty piazza <strong>facing the pier. Here you’ll find some </strong>shops and <strong>cafés, and a compact quarter of old houses. </strong>Although administratively separate from Cernobbio, the lake’s capital of Como is but a short hop away for a generally faster pace of life with far more shops, bars, and restaurants, plus museums, churches and the like. If you appreciate good views and gentle walking, we offer an easy three-hour guided Inghams Wanderwalk up the funicular railway to Brunate for a super lake and mountain panorama and a chance to explore the Pissarito spring, the Villa d’Este, Monta Rosa and the 15th century former convent of Eremo di San Donato.</p>]]></activityInformation>
